  "notes": [
    "v0.2.0 replaces automatic role negotiation with explicit Host selection and peer auto-join.",
    "SCR_Gameplay is the visual screen for both multiplayer and single-player modes.",
    "SCR_Error is the visual screen for Error, Halted, and Disconnected states; the message text distinguishes them.",
    "Dynamic labels whose content depends on firmware state are updated through dedicated UI adapter functions called by the state machine or BLE service, not by integration glue (LL-041).",
    "All NimBLE radio work is owned by the dedicated radio task and is never invoked directly from a state-machine action running inside LVGL timer context (LL-039, LL-042).",
    "The state-machine event queue is protected by a FreeRTOS mutex because BLE callbacks post events from a different task (LL-040).",
    "Under WOKWI_SIMULATION, NimBLE initialization is skipped; the state-machine flow is preserved by treating BLE init as success and using the Solo path for automated tests (LL-037)."
  ],
